<h2>1) Primary color</h2>
<p>A primary color is the color displayed most frequently across screens and components. This portion usually is brand identity color.</p>
<p><strong>At a glance</strong></p>
<ul class="sg-colors">
  <li>
    <div class="sg-colors__sample" style="background: {{colors.primary.hex}};"></div>
    <div class="sg-info">
      <span>{{colors.primary.description}}</span> <br/>
      <code>{{colors.primary.name}}</code>
    </div>
  </li>
</ul>
<h2>1.1) Primary Color Details</h2>
<h3>{{ colors.primary.description }}</h3>
<p>
  <span class="hex">HEX: {{ colors.primary.hex }}</span> | RGB: {{ colors.primary.rgb }}
</p>
<h2>2) Secondary color</h2>
<p>A secondary color is used to accent select parts of the design. It can be complementary or analogous to the primary
  color, but it should not simply be a light or dark variation of your primary color. It should contrast with elements
  that surround it and be applied sparingly as an accent.</p>
<p>Using a secondary color is optional. Itâ€™s not necessary if there are multiple variations of the primary color to
  accent elements.</p>

<div class="pl-note">
  <p><strong>Secondary colors are best used for:</strong></p>
  <ul class="pl-note__list">
    <li>Buttons, floating action buttons, and button text</li>
    <li>Selection controls, buttons, and sliders</li>
    <li>Text fields, cursors, and text selection</li>
    <li>Links</li>
    <li>Headlines</li>
    <li>Progress bars</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<p><strong>At a glance</strong></p>
<ul class="sg-colors">
  <li>
    <div class="sg-colors__sample" style="background: {{colors.secondary.hex}};"></div>
    <div class="sg-info">
      <span>{{colors.secondary.description}}</span> <br/>
      <code>{{colors.secondary.name}}</code>
    </div>
  </li>
</ul>
